**Visit End: Communication and Scenario Planning:**  
① Promotion Strategy → Continue with the "Project Momentum Emotional Value" approach, using value storytelling, scenario participation, and IP-based core communication paths;  
② Exposure → Create an online网红 (internet celebrity) case site + project live broadcast planning matrix platform, with exposure and live broadcast lead generation through quarterly, monthly, and key node placements;  
③ Scenario Story Case Site Packaging Optimization  

**Conversion End: Team Management and Sales Strategy:**  
① Lock in key sales nodes for June Dragon Boat Festival, 618, and 630, and formulate sales policy guidelines;  
② Price restructuring for high-end units in Unit 8# East, with an additional push during the Dragon Boat Festival;  
③ Focus on "trade-in for new" clients and launch dedicated live broadcast topics for online promotion;  
④ Parking space sales lead generation, report regional decision-making for opening after the holiday, and plan to accumulate one week of retail sales for shop opening sales;  

**Major Project and Company Support:**  
1. Resumption and replenishment: Apartment buildings 18, 22, 23, and 25 have resumed work; pre-positioned replenishment for 18 and 25# as mid-year sprint inventory;  
2. Display optimization: High-rise model floor adjustment and apartment G-type unit adjustment by end of June; boundary apartment exterior by June 30;  
3. Second batch product strategy and unit plan refinement finalized;  
4. Botanical Garden IP: Implementation of botanical garden signing or other course base plaque ceremony to form IP communication and story-based case site support, May 30; Responsible persons → Qu Quanyue, Liu Yang, Zhang Rui, Li Xiaoxia;  
5. Live broadcast traffic payment coordination: Ling Xia is temporarily not pre-paying for traffic fees due to payment issues, resulting in a 40% drop in live broadcast exposure, 50% drop in leads, and 30% drop in visits (existing resources are being followed up);  
6. Trade-in for new: Company-level dedicated team coordinates Chengfa and Housing Bureau to expedite "trade-in for new" unit signing progress

Visiting End:  
① Online property consultants collaborate with in-house channels for joint live broadcasts to continuously acquire customers online; ② Visit and expand key distribution stores in the surrounding areas;  
2. Conversion End:  
① Special application for top and bottom unit pricing on a per-unit basis; ② Strengthen the packaging and release of housing discount strategies on a weekly basis; ③ Ensure on-site property viewings and professional explanations by engineering staff for every visiting customer group;  
3. Commercial Units:  
① Due to combined units and later design adjustments, some actual areas differ from the survey reports; after re-verifying the blueprints with the design team, the street maps and price lists have been adjusted accordingly; ② Carry out external marketing and customer accumulation for commercial units.

column4:
Task progress lags behind the timeline  
① At the beginning of the month, the number of potential clients held by property consultants decreased, and overall visitation did not show a significant increase; continuous customer accumulation is needed;  
② Clients' hesitant mindset has not changed. The 5.17 policy adjustment has temporarily negatively impacted demand-driven projects, causing clients to remain in a wait-and-see mode and not rush to purchase, making it difficult to quickly improve conversion rates.

column5:
1. Visitor End:  
① Focus on the hot addition of Unit 15# West, which is about to be topped out, and promote multiple key nodes for the Mid-Year 618 sales drive to attract visitors;  
② Leverage the parking space policy to re-contact all owners, especially those who have taken over their units, continue the open-air film festival, and promote the old-to-new referral policy;  
③ Provide watermelons and cooling items at key distribution stores to strengthen customer engagement;  
④ Continue night outreach activities at Jinyi City.  

2. Conversion End:  
① Organize sales teams to visit several high-sales concentration projects in the city to analyze objections and refine talking points;  
② Use the additional Unit 15# West units combined with the 618 promotional discounts to apply dual pressure on customers;  
③ Prepare a visual aid table comparing the time difference between purchasing a nearby unfinished unit and purchasing ours to assist in customer conversion.  

3. Others:  
Collaborate with the design team to add 120 soft furnishing model units to enhance customer's sense of scene and experience.

column4:
① The number of visitors continues to decline, with zero visitors from Tuesday to Thursday during the week. Before the Dragon Boat Festival, distribution focused on site visits and policy releases, resulting in 11 visitor groups that week:  
② 119-unit type: This week, 4 visitor groups expressed demand for the 119-unit type, showing resistance to the delivery time of Building 22, prolonging the conversion cycle;  
③ The main client Wanbang is entering a slow season, hesitant to use funds for home purchases due to concerns about cash flow, leading to a decline in purchasing intent.

column5:
1. Visitor End: ① Go out to visit clients at their workplaces; visited 62 groups during the Dragon Boat Festival, with 2 groups of old clients bringing in new clients; consistently organize community activities, such as organizing a homeowner badminton challenge this week; ② Identify key clients who have already made purchases, and regularly organize afternoon tea visits for 4 groups per week to maintain relationships and expand the project's influence; ③ Organize concentrated night outreach activities at Tianze City in the evenings; ④ Bind the property consultants' self-acquisition capabilities with on-site visit resource allocation; ⑤ Focus on maintaining relationships with 17# homeowners to increase 119 new client referrals;  
2. Conversion End: ① "618 Early Access to Great Homes" – package exclusive discounted home sales policies to attract clients in advance; ② Organize a building tour for 22#, clarify the building's value, understand construction progress, and convert this into client guidance statements;  
3. Others: Package the sales scene for the 630 project delivery at the sales site to reinforce the value of the ready-to-move-in property.

1. Visitor End:  
① First, communicate with each agent who brings visitors, and lock 2 units for external release using the "work compensation housing" approach to attract agents for property viewings;  
② Seize the opportunity of increased distribution points to centrally gather key sales-focused villa agents and store agents to shoot promotional videos at the project site, enhancing promotional heat;  
③ Re-engage former Lianjiao Villa sales consultants and top sales performers, inform them of current pricing and available units to promote customer referrals;  
④ Introduce employee policies to encourage the utilization of employee network resources;  
⑤ Conduct cross-visitations with clients who visited last year but did not make a purchase to assess their current interest level.  

2. Conversion End:  
① Assign property management to conduct detailed organization of the unit status to ensure good display conditions and enhance customer experience;  
② Arrange property management to organize the surrounding interface of the project to improve the presentation status.

1. Fully launch the parking space trial parking event, invite customers in advance through trial parking invitations, increase communication channels with customers, and maximize customer acquisition by improving the effectiveness of trial parking processing;  
2. 618 Super Parking Space Festival event: Fully launch promotional materials such as policy posters, trial parking point panels, and underground corridor banners, achieve comprehensive publicity coverage, and maximize marketing momentum to leverage the 618 event for maximum customer acquisition:  
